6. تحديث قاعدة البيانات:

تأكد من إضافة الأعمدة التي تحتاجها في جدول في قاعدة البيانات:packages

bash
php artisan make:migration update_packages_table --table=packages

ثم في ملف الـ migration، قم بتحديث الجدول لإضافة الأعمدة الجديدة مثل و :routeguide_name

php
public function up()
{
    Schema::table('packages', function (Blueprint $table) {
        $table->string('route');
        $table->string('guide_name');
    });
}

public function down()
{
    Schema::table('packages', function (Blueprint $table) {
        $table->dropColumn(['route', 'guide_name']);
    });
}

ثم قم بتشغيل migration:

bash
php artisan migrate

7. إضافة بيانات تجريبية (Seeder)

يمكنك إضافة بيانات تجريبية باستخدام Seeder:

php
public function run()
{
    Package::create([
        'name' => 'Jordan Adventure Tour',
        'description' => 'Explore the deserts and mountains of Jordan with our expert guides.',
        'price' => 100,
        'start_date' => now(),
        'end_date' => now()->addDays(7),
        'image' => 'packages/jordan_adventure.jpg',
        'route' => 'Amman -> Petra -> Wadi Rum',
        'guide_name' => 'John Doe',
    ]);
}

النهاية:

بعد هذه الخطوات، ستكون لديك صفحة لعرض الحزم السياحية بكل تفاصيلها، مع إمكانية الحجز لكل حزمة.

You said:
i clone laravel project and its run with docker but i want to run it using xampp not docker and how clone it all
ChatGPT said:

To run a Laravel project with XAMPP instead of Docker, follow these steps:

1. Clone the Laravel Project

If you haven't cloned the project yet, you can do so with this command:

bash
git clone <repository-url>

Navigate to the folder where you want to clone the project and replace with the URL of the repository.<repository-url>

2. Set Up XAMPP

Ensure that XAMPP is installed on your system. You can download it from here.

  1. Start Apache and MySQL: Open XAMPP Control Panel and start the Apache and MySQL services.

  2. Configure php.ini (Optional): If you want to increase PHP’s memory limit or upload size, open the php.ini file by clicking the Config button next to Apache in the XAMPP control panel, and adjust the settings like and .upload_max_filesizememory_limit

3. Move the Project to XAMPP Directory

  1. Move the Laravel Project Folder: Place the Laravel project folder in the XAMPP htdocs directory.

    • The default path for XAMPP’s htdocs directory is:

      • Windows: C:\xampp\htdocs\

      • Mac: /Applications/XAMPP/htdocs/

    Move the cloned Laravel project to folder. For example, if your project is named , the path should look like .htdocstraveljordanC:\xampp\htdocs\traveljordan

4. Set Up Environment Variables

  1. Navigate to the Project Folder: Go to your project directory inside .htdocs

    bash
    cd C:\xampp\htdocs\traveljordan

  2. Create .env File: If there is no file, create it by copying the file..env.env.example

    bash
    cp .env.example .env

  3. Configure Database: In the file, update the database configuration to use XAMPP’s MySQL:.env

    • DB_CONNECTION=mysql

    • DB_HOST=127.0.0.1

    • DB_PORT=3306

    • DB_DATABASE=your_database_name

    • DB_USERNAME=root

    • DB_PASSWORD= (leave it blank by default in XAMPP)

    Example:

    env
    DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=travel_jordan
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=

5. Install Composer Dependencies

  1. Install Composer (if you don’t have it already): Download and install Composer from here.

  2. Install Laravel Dependencies: After navigating to your project directory, run the following command to install all Laravel dependencies:

    bash
    composer install

    This will install all necessary libraries defined in your .composer.json

6. Generate the Application Key

Run the following command to generate a new APP_KEY for your Laravel application:

bash
php artisan key:generate

This will automatically update the file with a new APP_KEY..env

7. Create the Database

Open phpMyAdmin by going to in your browser.http://localhost/phpmyadmin/

  • Create a new database for your project (e.g., ).travel_jordan

  • If your project requires some tables (such as user data), you may need to run migrations (explained in the next step).

8. Run Migrations (Optional)

If the project uses migrations to set up the database schema, you can run them by executing the following command:

bash
php artisan migrate

This will create the necessary tables in your database (as long as your file is correctly configured with database credentials)..env

9. Set Permissions (Linux/Mac Only)

If you're using Linux or Mac, you might need to set the correct file permissions for Laravel's storage and cache directories:

bash
sudo chmod -R 775 storage bootstrap/cache

10. Access the Project

Now, you should be able to access the Laravel project by opening your browser and navigating to:

arduino
http://localhost/traveljordan/public

or if your Laravel project’s public folder is directly accessible:

arduino
http://localhost/traveljordan

You should see your Laravel application running on XAMPP.

11. Troubleshooting

If the application isn't working, here are some common issues:

  • Database connection issues: Double-check the file to ensure that the database name, username, and password are correct..env

  • Missing dependencies: Run again to ensure all dependencies are installed.composer install

  • Permissions issues: Ensure the proper permissions are set for Laravel's storage and cache folders.

Summary:

  • Clone the project into .htdocs

  • Set up with the correct database settings for XAMPP..env

  • Run to install dependencies.composer install

  • Run to create the database tables if necessary.php artisan migrate

  • Access the project via .http://localhost/your_project_name/public

This should get your Laravel project running on XAMPP without Docker!
